snippet.textDisplay:
God, I hate going to the dentist. I remember falling down really bad (when I was 11) and shattering two of my top incisors. I had to get 2 root canals done, before I got fake teeth. When I went to the dentist, he gave me a strawberry gel to rub on my gums, and then proceeded inject an anaesthetic into my mouth. For the rest of the operation, I was probably in the most pain I’ve ever been in since my life. I don’t know the exact process, but from what I saw, they had to melt away part of my broken teeth (I could tell from the smell of burning chalk) and then stick a drill/probe, to remove the infected pulp cavity. The sound of a dentist’s drill probably gives me chills when it’s even mentioned.
Fast forward a few years, and I’m now in medical college, and part of your clinical rotations include dentistry, which starts in 2 weeks. I low-key have PTSD from when I was younger, and I can’t make myself want to even go into the hospital, even if I’m not a patient this time.

snippet.textDisplay: when I was 16 I got one of my wisdom teeth out. they also didn't drug me so I was just like sitting there scared but not really caring?? the procedure went ok. went normal probably so then we went home. my parents went to get the pain medicine after while I closed my eyes for a few eeeeh hours. when I woke up they weren't back yet but my brother was and he had malasadas and I was pissed because I couldn't eat because of my teeth. I didn't eat anything because I was pissed about the malasadas and n turn didn't take medicine (cuz I feel like I can't take medicine without eating first). the numbing started to fade and I still hadn't taken medicine and very quickly it started hurting like hell so I ate soup and took the medicine but it took a while to start working so it was just like groaning in bed for a while. notice at the beginning I said I got ONE of my wisdom teeth out, which wasn't very wise on my part, and now they're really starting to bother me. like one of them is poking the inside of my cheek. it's not like painful but its definitely annoying but because of that whole thing where it hurt after the numbing wore off has me scared of getting my other three out...
